    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f7fb3bff_49bd418b",
        "filename": "snapshot/minidump/module_snapshot_minidump.cc",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 134,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-04-22T19:13:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Did .CvRecord.DataSize indicate that it was large enough?\n\nI know I’ve asked this a few times. Maybe a more reasonable layout would be to do this all in a single InitializeModuleCodeView() function:\n\n1. check that CvRecord.DataSize is big enough for signature, fail early if not\n2. read signature\n3. conditional on signature:\n   3a. check that CvRecord.DataSize is big enough for fixed-length data to read next (only applies to PDB70)\n   3b. read fixed-length data\n   3c. read variable-length data as remainder of CvRecord.DataSize\n4. if signature is unknown, fail\n\nNote that doing it all in a single function means that you don’t need to double-check the signature everywhere, which in turn means that you don’t need to check that CvRecord.DataSize can store the signature multiple times, and you don’t even need to read the signature more than once.",
      "revId": "81e7cacb724b1d3e03b6435a5195de7cb2e80a54",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
